Persian Gulf Stocks: Aldar, Jarir Marketing, Saudi Electricity

-- B y   Z a h r a   H a n k i r
-- 
2011-10-18T13:36:56Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-18/persian-gulf-stocks-aldar-jarir-marketing-saudi-electricity.html
The  DFM General Index (DFMGI)  retreated to
the lowest since March 3, dropping 0.6 percent to 1,357.71 at
the 2 p.m. close in the emirate. Saudi Arabia’s  Tadawul All
Share Index (SASEIDX)  gained 0.3 percent.  The following shares were active in the Persian Gulf
region. Stock symbols are in parentheses.  Aldar Properties PJSC (ALDAR)   slumped to the lowest on
record, retreating 2 percent to 98 fils. The Abu Dhabi developer
that’s had three chief executive officers in four years said its
board will meet on Oct. 20 to consider the appointment of a new
chief financial officer.  Jarir Marketing Co. (JARIR)   surged to a record high,
soaring 9.9 percent to 200 riyals. The largest Saudi Arabian
retailer of stationery and smartphones by market value
recommended a third-quarter dividend of 3.4 riyals and one bonus
share for every two held.  Saudi Electricity Co. (SECO)   slumped the most in more
than two months, decreasing 1.8 percent to 13.45 riyals. The
kingdom’s largest utility said third-quarter profit fell 6
percent to 2.18 billion riyals ($581 million) as the cost of
production increased.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Zahra Hankir in Dubai at 
 zhankir@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Claudia Maedler at 
 cmaedler@bloomberg.net  